Wenger: &quot;Danny Welbeck is a team player, that's why coaches love him. He gets stronger &amp; stronger. He's a guy with huge physical potential.&quot;<br />
<br />
Wenger on Welbeck: &quot;People are not convinced he's a great finisher, but these goals will help him become more relaxed in front of goal.&quot;

Wenger on Coquelin: &quot;He has a hamstring [problem]. I don't know how bad it is but he's certainly out for next week's game.&quot; #afc<br />
<br />
Wenger on Wilshere: &quot;The fact that Francis is out gives him a chance as well. [play on Thursday?] I don't know yet, he's not far from that.&quot;

Lacazette: &quot;(Giroud), like me, understood that it was the coach who made the decision and that there was no reason to blame the other.&quot;<br />
<br />
Lacazette: &quot;I came to Arsenal to win titles, play great matches, to make progress and discover another culture and another league.&quot;

Arsene Wenger insists he was never tempted to quit Arsenal for Manchester United...<br />
<br />
&quot;No (I was never tempted by United) because I was always happy here. More people were happy with me, I was always happy here.&quot;
